This paper is about software effort estimation using machine learning techniques, specifically Model Tree. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the use of optimization algorithms to improve the accuracy of the Model Tree, which falls under the category of machine learning optimization techniques. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of cross-validation to assess prediction accuracies, which is a common technique in computational experiments, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of Model Tree with other well-known estimation methods, which falls under the category of computational engineering, making cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) a possible sub-category as well.
